entries.title: Berlin Detains German Intelligence Official Suspected of Spying for Russia
entries.description: Arrest is blow to a government that had sought to clamp down on Russian influence in its ranks since Moscow’s invasion of Ukraine

entries.title: Islamic State Suspected to Be Behind Series of Attacks in Iraq
entries.description: The attack, the fourth in two weeks, is the latest sign that the militant group is attempting a violent resurgence.

entries.title: Fentanyl Crisis Fed by Flow of Chinese Chemicals to Mexican Drug Cartels
entries.description: Strains in U.S.-China relations have ended Beijing’s cooperation in restricting chemicals that are key ingredients for making the deadly drug.

entries.title: As India Leaves Covid Behind, Families Say Their Dead Weren't Counted
entries.description: Some people say their loved ones died from the disease but they lack the documentation to prove it.

entries.title: Ukraine Diplomatic Flurry Centers on War, Not Peace
entries.description: Volodymyr Zelensky’s Washington meetings and a Beijing trip by Russia’s former prime minister aimed to secure support for renewed fighting, including a potential Russian offensive early next year.

entries.title: U.K. Strikes Expand to Passport Control, Disrupting Holiday Travel
entries.description: British passport control staff are set to become the latest government workers to seek wage rises that get closer to matching inflation, a sign that the economic and political turmoil that marked 2022 is far from over.

entries.title: Iran's Online Crackdown Prompts Smuggling of Starlink Kits
entries.description: Around 200 of the devices, which enable users to access the internet through satellite links, have been smuggled into Iran by supporters of a monthslong rights movement, according to the people involved in some of the shipments.

entries.title: Russia Blames Ukraine for Attack on Leaders Deep in Occupied Territory
entries.description: Explosions killed two people in Russian-held areas of eastern Ukraine and injured at least two prominent figures in what appears to show Kyiv’s ability to gather intelligence behind enemy lines.

entries.title: Europe Is Rushing Arms to Ukraine but Running Out of Ammo
entries.description: The continent is struggling to produce enough ammunition for Ukraine and for itself, jeopardizing NATO’s defense capacity and its support for Kyiv, officials and industry leaders say.

entries.title: Russia's Draft Patched Holes but Also Exposed Flaws in War Machine
entries.description: Soldiers mobilized to fight in Ukraine say inadequate training, alcohol abuse and faulty equipment abound.

entries.title: Fiji Deploys Military, Risking Tensions in Election Aftermath
entries.description: Prime Minister Frank Bainimarama’s party has yet to concede after the main opposition parties formed a coalition to oust the incumbent government.
